Sure. Let's talk about that. So perhaps for people who don't know, Ibis is a project which

00:28:34.680 --> 00:28:39.719
describes itself as being a portable data frame library. So the idea is that they've got this

00:28:40.359 --> 00:28:46.359
Python API, which then gets translated to their intermediate representation,

00:28:46.439 --> 00:28:50.199
and they can then translate it either to SQL engines or to Polars.

00:28:51.959 --> 00:28:55.400
And like this, with just one API, you can target different engines.

00:28:56.599 --> 00:29:02.680
