00:29:02.680 --> 00:29:11.079
over the other? And if you're an end user, if you need to do some complicated analysis,

00:29:11.079 --> 00:29:17.160
if you're an ML engineer or whatever, then I'm not sure that Narwhals is necessarily the

00:29:17.160 --> 00:29:22.839
best tool for that task. So with Narwhals, we're trying really to target library maintainers.

00:29:26.599 --> 00:29:31.640
