00:34:23.560 --> 00:34:27.320
This, yeah, we've talked about career advice. So here's another career advice.

00:34:28.439 --> 00:34:35.320
I think this one might come from Warren Buffett, maybe, which was about, I think the story is that

00:34:35.320 --> 00:34:41.560
he asked someone like, what are your top 30 goals? And yeah, how many of these do you plan

00:34:41.560 --> 00:34:45.800
to address in the next year? And this person says, oh yeah, I might do the top five. Maybe

00:34:45.800 --> 00:34:51.080
I can do the top 10, top 15, if I can do it. And Warren's reply is no, no, you've got it all wrong.

00:34:51.159 --> 00:34:55.560
You need to circle the top five and everything else you consciously do not work on because it's

00:34:55.560 --> 00:35:01.719
going to distract you from the top five. So I think you just need to be ruthless in saying

00:35:01.719 --> 00:35:08.600
no to things. Like not everything can be fixed, not everything should be addressed. And keep

00:35:11.719 --> 00:35:15.800
the end goal in mind. Don't chase rabbits when you're out hunting elephants.

